cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes an autonomous ultrasound scanning system using the da Vinci Research Kit (dVRK), which is a robotic surgical system. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The proposed system uses a vision-based approach to learn the underlying tissue motion characteristics and incorporates it into the visual servoing framework. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed system uses a machine learning approach to learn the underlying tissue motion characteristics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed system uses artificial intelligence techniques such as machine learning and visual servoing. 
- cs.MS (Medical Imaging): The paper focuses on the use of intraoperative ultrasound for tumour localisation during minimally invasive procedures.
